result.name: Sweet Basil Thai Cuisine

reviews.text:
Lovely restaurant situated in the mall.  Good ambience and decor.  not the quietest restaurant.

Service was a bit slow.  The food is amazing Thai Cuisine -  went husband and son really  enjoyed their meals however the dish I ordered said clams and Scallops and I was served with scallops and something that was far from clams.

No starch is served with any of their dishes and must be ordered separately at an exorbitant amount.

It was wonderful had a very nice experience 
I would recommend you to get the pineapple rice or something like that it's unique and interesting to experience

Sweet Basil Thai Cuisine served great Thai food, and the decorations are nice.
Came here for lunch, and they offer set lunch with average of $140 per head.  Food here is great, although it's not really Thai feeling, but all dishes are well cooked.  The price is acceptable, but for this price, you can actually find other better Thai food around

One of our favourite Thai restaurants in town. Delicious fresh pomelo salad, tossed with coconut milk and fish sauce), juicy baby oysters in the omelette, crispy fried soft shell crabs and the yellow beef curry (served with garlic bread). Thai food hadn't tasted better.

The crab flavour was amazing. Right blend of spicy.  The morning glory was fine. The ground pork taro rice was good but not amazing. The price is pricey but not for Hongkong 418 for crab?  The desserts were 5 stars. Nice restaurant with fun staff. Enough attention but not intrusive.

result.name: Lee Theatre

reviews.text: This area of Hong Kong was recently redone. The shopping area is really cute with tons of stores. It is very clean the sales people are very helpful it's a few blocks away from times square mall. It's has lots of up  scale stores they are all very nice there is multiple buildings in the Lee Theater area so check the address to make sure you are in the correct building

Large shopping mall which is part of the Lee Gardens concept. Nice and functional, but not really with to much of a soul of is own or anything else to do really than to shop and eat. Functional rather than fantastic.

Your dinning place. Lots of nice restaurants in this building. 

Lower level are clothing shops. Upper levels are all restaurants. Take the lifts to go up to the higher levels.

this is a place to visit especially if you love shopping at UNIQLO. Several floors of UNIQLO assures you way better variety and stocks. Being located in causeway bay, it is convenient to explore from one shopping mall to another since the malls are just adjacent to each other.
The once iconic landmark theater turned shopping and dining center.
